  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Max Def Heather Blend reads as a warm sienna in midday sun and a deep coffee at dusk. It is one of the more tonally responsive SKUs in the line and rewards homeowners who care about how a roof shifts color across the day.",
      "CertainTeed mixes a base of mid-brown granules with smaller portions of true black and warm rust accents. The result is a roof that holds its warmth even on overcast days, which is when most gray shingles look their most neutral.",
      "Works well with red brick, warm-wood accents, stone, and earth-tone paint. Tends to disagree with very cool siding colors (icy white, light blue, charcoal) where the warm undertone reads as out of place."
    ],
